# On-Chain Goals & Escrow System with SBT Badges

Rebuild the goals system to use Polygon Amoy smart contracts for both personal savings goals and multi-user escrow pools, with SBT badge minting on completion and ML-powered progress tracking.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **This is a multi-phase build** covering Solidity contracts, backend API, and frontend. We should tackle it in phases so you can test each layer before moving to the next. Phase 1 (contracts) is the foundation everything else depends on.

> [!WARNING]
> **Escrow contracts hold real funds on-chain.** Even on testnet, the contract logic must be airtight — no reentrancy, no early withdrawal exploits. We'll use OpenZeppelin's `ReentrancyGuard`.

> [!CAUTION]
> **Your existing [GoalBadgeSBT.sol](file:///Users/aditya4/Desktop/blockchain1st/contracts/GoalBadgeSBT.sol) in `blockchain1st/` stores massive SVG data URIs on-chain** (causing the 0.28 POL gas issue we debugged). The new contracts will store ONLY minimal metadata on-chain — the badge SVG will be rendered client-side.

## Architecture Overview

```
Frontend (Next.js :3000)
    │
    ├── MetaMask / Ethers.js ──────────── Polygon Amoy (Contracts)
    │       │                                   │
    │       ├── PersonalGoalSBT.sol ────────── Single user goals + SBT
    │       └── EscrowPool.sol ─────────────── Group goals + escrow + SBT
    │
    └── REST API ──────────────────────── Backend (FastAPI :8000)
            │                                   │
            ├── /api/v1/goals/* ────────────── Goal CRUD + progress
            ├── /api/v1/escrow/* ───────────── Group pool management
            └──── ML Models Service (:8001) ── Forecaster for savings calc
```

### Progress Tracking Logic (2 modes):

| Mode | When | How savings are calculated |
|---|---|---|
| **Short-term** (≤4 weeks) | User uploads CSV daily/weekly | `savings = forecasted_budget - actual_spend` from CSV |
| **Long-term** (monthly) | User provides salary + CSV | `savings = salary - total_monthly_spend` from CSV |

Both modes apply to personal AND escrow goals.

