## Proposed Changes

### Phase 1: Smart Contracts (Solidity)

New contracts directory inside the monorepo.

---

#### [NEW] [PersonalGoalSBT.sol](file:///Users/aditya4/Desktop/Budget-Bandhu/contracts/PersonalGoalSBT.sol)

Personal savings goal contract + soulbound badge minting.

**Key design:**
- User calls [createGoal(name, targetAmount, deadline)](file:///Users/aditya4/Desktop/blockchain1st/components/GoalBadgeDemo.js#36-56) — stores goal on-chain
- Backend/frontend calls `updateProgress(goalId, newSavedAmount)` — updates off-chain calculated savings
- Only the goal owner OR a trusted verifier can call `updateProgress`
- When `current >= target`, calls `completeGoal(goalId)` → mints an SBT badge to the user
- SBT uses OZ ERC-721 with transfers disabled (soulbound)
- `tokenURI` is a lightweight JSON (NO SVG on-chain) — ~200 bytes, not 9KB
- Inherits `Ownable`, `ReentrancyGuard`

**Functions:**
```
createGoal(string name, uint256 target, uint256 deadline) → uint256 goalId
updateProgress(uint256 goalId, uint256 savedAmount)
completeGoal(uint256 goalId) → mints SBT
getGoal(uint256 goalId) → GoalInfo struct
getUserGoals(address user) → uint256[] goalIds
```

---

#### [NEW] [EscrowPool.sol](file:///Users/aditya4/Desktop/Budget-Bandhu/contracts/EscrowPool.sol)

Multi-party escrow pool contract for group savings goals.

**Key design:**
- Creator calls `createPool(name, targetAmount, deadline, maxMembers)` → generates a `poolId`
- Other users join via `joinPool(poolId)` — invite link contains the poolId
- Members contribute via `contribute(poolId)` sending POL with the tx (actual on-chain funds)
- **Nobody can withdraw** until `pool.totalContributed >= pool.target` — this is the escrow guarantee
- On completion, creator calls `completePool(poolId)` → funds released to creator, SBT badges minted to ALL members
- Emergency: if deadline passes and target not met, members can call `refund(poolId)` to get their individual contributions back

**Functions:**
```
createPool(string name, uint256 target, uint256 deadline, uint8 maxMembers) → uint256 poolId
joinPool(uint256 poolId) payable
contribute(uint256 poolId) payable
completePool(uint256 poolId) → release funds + mint SBTs
refund(uint256 poolId) → return individual contributions if deadline expired
getPool(uint256 poolId) → PoolInfo struct
getPoolMembers(uint256 poolId) → address[]
```

